    "title": {
      "rendered": "Nonprofits! This Is How to Use Facebook&#8217;s Fundraising Tools"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-22082\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Facebook-Fundraising-Tools-Facebook-2-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Facebook-Fundraising-Tools-Facebook-2.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Facebook-Fundraising-Tools-Facebook-2.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Facebook-Fundraising-Tools-Facebook-2.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Facebook-Fundraising-Tools-Facebook-2.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Facebook-Fundraising-Tools-Facebook-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />Through a process of trial and error, the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/rescuefreedomproject/\"><strong>Beagle Freedom Project</strong></a> is learning how to effectively use <strong><a href=\"https://nonprofits.fb.com/topic/fundraising-tools/\">Facebook&#8217;s Fundraising Tools</a></strong> and they are being rewarded with more than likes and hearts &#8211; their followers are donating!</p>\n<p>For the last two weeks the organization has been <strong><a href=\"https://secure.facebook.com/rescuefreedomproject/posts/2304145799611560\">writing compelling posts</a></strong> that evoke strong emotions, uploaded photos that accentuate the story, added a &#8220;Donate&#8221; button their posts, and tagged their posts as &#8220;asking for donations.&#8221; Donors are quickly learning that after a first donation is made on Facebook all other donations can be made with two taps.</p>\n<p>Nonprofits would be wise to get serious about learning how to use Facebook&#8217;s Fundraising Tools to raise money on the world&#8217;s largest social network while organic reach is still high!</p>\n<p>In addition to donation posts, the Beagle Freedom Project is also <a href=\"https://secure.facebook.com/pg/rescuefreedomproject/fundraisers/?ref=page_internal\"><strong>recruiting followers to fundraise for their organization</strong></a> and by the looks of it (see below), they are raising thousands of dollars. A lot of nonprofits are reluctant to use Facebook&#8217;s Fundraising Tools because a donor can opt-out of providing their email address and Facebook will not provide the mailing address of donors. That&#8217;s a cautious response with some wisdom to it, but the nonprofits that will pioneer Facebook fundraising will be more bold in their thinking.</p>\n<p>Finally, it is worth noting that:<strong> 1)</strong> Facebook&#8217;s Fundraising Tools are free to use. There is <strong><a href=\"https://qz.com/1141658/facebook-is-dropping-its-fundraising-fees-for-non-profits-but-not-for-personal-causes/\">no fee to the nonprofit</a></strong>. <strong>2)</strong> Facebook has launched a <a href=\"http://www.thenonprofittimes.com/news-articles/40548/\"><strong>$50 million annual matching fund</strong></a> for those nonprofits that use their tools. <strong>3)</strong> 25% of online donors say social media is the tool that inspires them most often to give. Of those, <strong><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo/index.html\">62% say Facebook is the most inspiring</a>. 4) </strong>Facebook&#8217;s Fundraising Tools are currently available to nonprofits in the <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/help/1251484118194936\">United States and numerous countries in Europe</a></strong>.</p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Fundraising post with a &#8220;Donate&#8221; button</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://secure.facebook.com/rescuefreedomproject/posts/2304145799611560\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22053\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Post-2.jpg?resize=600%2C854\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"854\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Post-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Post-2.jpg?resize=211%2C300&amp;ssl=1 211w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Facebook Fundraisers</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/rescuefreedomproject/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22056\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Fundraisers-2.jpg?resize=600%2C522\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"522\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Fundraisers-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Fundraisers-2.jpg?resize=300%2C261&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Facebook Donors<br />\n(Settings &gt; Payments)</h2>\n<h5 id=\"js_1ro\" class=\"_14f5 _5pbw _5vra\" style=\"text-align: center;\" data-ft=\"{&quot;tn&quot;:&quot;C&quot;}\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22068\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Donors-2.jpg?resize=600%2C569\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"569\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Donors-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Beagle-Donors-2.jpg?resize=300%2C285&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></h5>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Newly Released! The 2018 Global NGO Technology Report</h2>\n<p>Published in \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651\u0629, English, fran\u00e7ais, portugu\u00eas y espa\u00f1ol, the <strong><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo\">2018 Global NGO Technology Report</a></strong>\u00a0is based on the survey results of 5,352 NGOs from 164 countries.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22066\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?resize=600%2C315\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
